 going to be able to due is run away and try to get off the radar for a sec and come back.  <br>Clerics run everytime when mez is purged?...i don't doubt that, not in the least.  Cleric melee (missing those all important +to hit styles) is far overrated even with the damage add when compared to a skalds 2handed+damage add.  even with both instants (which means no 48 spec smite btw), the melee of a skald vs a cleric is usually not a contest at all and without a quickcast or a mez that is all there is to use barring the PB damage (which is marginally comparable in damage to one of a skalds even though it is AE)<br><br>one on one without mez the cleric will go down 90% of the time (or if the skald purges the stun, fear the stun not the mez)  <br><br>Its all a chain, if jumped you must (MUST) mez/stun/nuke/nuke/nuke<br>or mez/nuke/stun/nuke/nuke/nuke &lt;--(not vs any instant casters or your screwed)<br>attempting to melee is usually a futile attempt, and it all goes back to the &quot;if i can catch them with a stun&quot;...<br><br>skalds were usually one of my most feared opponents so the feeling goes both ways <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>of course now I am a skald on Mordred and loving every minute of it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saebjorn>Saebjorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/02 6:00:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> If u get close enough when he starts nukeing u, when ur stunned, spam the m